content:
The following topics tell you how to manage your OmniScripts.

Importing OmniScripts: OmniScripts can be imported using the Data Pack feature, allowing you to move them from one environment to another.
Exporting OmniScripts: OmniScripts can be exported using the Data Pack feature, allowing you to move them from one environment to another.
Version OmniScripts: Create multiple versions of an OmniScript to develop and test scripts in preview mode before activating for production deployment.
Save and Resume an OmniScript: Save and resume OmniScripts beginning with Vlocity Insurance and Health Winter '20 and Vlocity CME Winter '20.
Emailing an OmniScript: Email a link to an OmniScript using an Integration Procedure that sends the email and calls the procedure from Apex code or an OmniScript.
title: Managing OmniScripts in Salesforce
